The paper discusses security and privacy issues in Big Data applications, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper focuses on security and privacy aspects. The second likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as Big Data applications involve managing and processing large amounts of data. The third likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper discusses privacy issues in social networks. The fourth likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper addresses the societal impact of sharing personal data. The fifth likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper discusses the use of SDN as a mechanism to implement security in Big Data systems.
